## Context: What Anvil Looks Like Today

The agent currently uses these concepts (keep them, evolve them):

- **DAL-based verification hierarchy**: DAL-A for SIMD kernels, DAL-B for Python training, DAL-C for config/tooling, DAL-D for docs
- **Golden Signals**: Latency (step_time, TTFT, P50/P95/P99), Throughput (tokens/sec, GFLOPS), Errors (non-finite, gradient failures), Saturation (thread util, SIMD coverage, RSS)
- **Traceability**: requirement → design → code → test → verification result
- **Severity matrix**: P0 (catastrophic / DAL-A) through P3 (docs / DAL-D)
- **CPU-first, SIMD-first compute** for all hot paths
- **Complexity mandate**: O(1)/O(log n)/O(n) preferred; O(n²)+ in hot paths prohibited
- **Zero dead code** policy
- **Cleanroom philosophy**: fix root cause, never mask symptoms
- **Chronicle protocol**: baseline metrics → change → result metrics logged
- **Red-team protocol**: complexity check, FMEA, FTA, OWASP, regression gate

Evolve and strengthen these. Don't discard them.

